FOODBORNE ILLNESS, FISH - CHINA (GUANGDONG) (02): TETRODOTOXIN
**************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Mon 12 Mar 2007
From: Dan Silver <dgsilver@yahoo.com>
Source: Xinmin Evening News [in Chinese, translated by submitter, edited]
http://xmwb.news365.com.cn/zg/200703/t20070313_1327322.htm

"Yongeichthys criniger" Contains Tetrodotoxin
16 Poisoned by Eating Seafish, One Dead
-----------------------------------------
Recently, a number of villagers in Xilian Township of Xuwen County in
Zhenjiang Municipality suffered food poisoning after eating
_Yongeichthys criniger_. 16 people developed symptoms and one died
en route to hospital.
On the morning of 12 Mar 2007, the Guangdong Provincial Health Bureau
received a report from the Zhenjiang Municipal Health Bureau that
between 7 & 9 Mar 2007, 13 people in Dajing Village of Xilian
Township in Xuwen County and 3 people in Guateng Village developed
symptoms of poisoning after eating seafish; 2 children were
included. A 56 year old male died en route to hospital.
3 people recovered and were discharged from hospital on 11 Mar
2007. Based on investigations and animal experimentation, health
agencies in Zhenjiang preliminarily believe that the poisoning
incident was caused by consumption of toxin-containing fish.
Experts at Zhenjiang Marine Fisheries Bureau and Zhenjiang Ocean
University confirm the fish species is _Yongeichthys criniger_, a
poisonous fish. The toxin it contains is Tetrodotoxin. [This is]
consistent with the conclusions of health agencies [following] on
site investigations. Local health agencies have strengthened health
supervision, launched public education, and recommended prohibitions
on the catching, purchasing, selling and consuming goby fish.
The Guangdong Provincial Health Bureau states that this is the 1st
report of food poisoning following consumption of this species of
fish in Guangdong Province.
[By: Xia Yang]
